description.narrative: This activity (South Sudan - Humanitarian Crisis Response) is a component of South Sudan - Humanitarian Crisis Response reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Humanitarian assistance' and a budget of £35,242,381. This component benefits South Sudan, and works in the following sector(s): Material relief assistance and services , Emergency food assistance, Relief co-ordination and support services. , with the following implementing partners: CANADEM, Concern Worldwide, Crown Agents Limited, Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations (FAO), GOAL, Information Management and Mine Action Programs, Inc., International Committee of the Red Cross, International Medical Corps UK, International Rescue Committee (UK), Norwegian Refugee Council, Oxfam GB, RedR, Save the Children UK, United Nations Children's Fund (UNICEF), United Nations High Commissioner for Refugees (UNHCR), World Food Programme (WFP), World Vision UK. The start date is 10-01-2014 and the end date is 31-12-2015.
